depends on the pizza. If you make your own basic pizza, it will be fine. Plain dough and sauce made only from tomatoes and basil will be fine. Cheese is debatable. Lactose Intolerance is the default state in the animal kingdom, so while cheese will not outright cause severe health problems, the dog will suffer the typical digestion issues the intolerance causes.

The problem comes from onions and garlic. Even when you ask for a plain cheese pizza the sauce can often have garlic in it for flavor. Sometimes people even put in onion powder, and guess what? Even a small amount of onion powder is not very good. The crust sometimes has garlic butter flavors infused into it and that is also not good.

Basically best thing you can do is make it yourself, to ensure you don't accidently submit the dog to garlic or onion poisoning. Feel free to add some meat toppings like bacon.
